Minister of Federal Capital Territory (FCT), Malam Muhammad Bello has ordered the demolition of alleged illegal corner shops in Utako. Bulldozers of the FCT Administration are demolishing the shops while traders are running around to salvage the what they can from their stuff.   Police recruitment based on merit, not politics,…     Buhari celebrates Amusan, Brume over World Athletics feats     Property destroyed as fire razes two-storey in Onitsha   Senior Special Assistant on Monitoring, Inspection and Enforcement to FCT Minister, Comrade Ikharo Attah, who is leading the FCTA demolition team, said the Minister is not happy with the sad development of illegal building in Abuja. Attah noted the residents had taken for granted the administration’s decision to use stakeholders engagement and respect for human rights in dealing with developmental issues before any enforcement. He bemoaned the activities by some persons that were gradually turning the Utako area to a security risk.